Portugal strengthened the National Health Service (SNS) by:  
"Exceptional human resources regime, which includes:
(i) suspension of overtime limits; 
(ii) simplifying the hiring of workers;
(iii) worker mobility;
(iv) hiring retired doctors without being subject to age limits.
Prevention regime for professionals in the health sector directly involved in the diagnosis and specialized laboratory response.
Exceptional regime for the purchase of services by organs, agencies, services and entities of the Ministry of Health.
Exceptional regime for the composition of medical boards for assessing the disabilities of people with disabilities."March 12

Portugal, September 24, 2020. The national government announced the following measures: 
- Commercial establishments can only open from 10:00 am (with exceptions);
- Closing hours of establishments can be between 8 pm and 11 pm, subject to municipal decision;
- Shopping centre food court  areas will have a maximum limit of 4 people per group;
- Prohibition on selling alcoholic beverages at service stations and, after 8 pm, in all establishments (except with meals);
- Prohibition of consumption of alcoholic beverages on public roads;
- Sporting venues will remain without spectators.

This measure took place between October 01 and October 14, 2020. 
 UPDATE: Extension dates, and event description.

